I had called to make sure that inquire on if I needed a reservation and was told no “we can accommodate a party of 3 at 7:30”. When I arrived I was told by a different employee that it would require some movement but they would try to fit us in. They also did not enforce wear a mask when up from the table or check temperatures. We eventually got seated and our server Marlon was very nice and accommodating. Even though I order a starter as my entree and make sure to state that my food came out well before my party’s. It then took 15 minutes for my sister to receive her food. We waited 15 more minutes for my mother’s food and when we asked when it would be out we were told it would take 15-20 minutes more. Marlon however tried his best to make it a better situation. He offered found a table for us, offered us a free appetizer, and even took the entree that never arrived off our bill. I will also mention that despite having a song saying they were limiting seating time because of the current pandemic they are not. They’re was a party that was there well before us and at the same time we had. Overall my family will not be coming here again, which is very unfortunate. They only get two stars because of Marlon

This is a nice after work, casual date or weekend spot. When my friend chose it and I saw it was Caribbean I wasn’t particularly enthused about eating there. Thankfully I was able to look at some pictures of their meals and determined I’d be able to find something I’d like. The establishment is a nice size with a bar in the front and dining towards the back and sides. It doesn’t feel tight and the ambience is chill, the clientele friendly. The background music wasn’t loud and I couldn’t even tell you what was playing. The seating space was adequate and the chairs were comfortable. I started with a rum punch which I had red was delicious and they didn’t disappoint and it was a full glass serving. Now let’s get to the food..... Let me tell you Google how surprisingly delicious my food was! Omg! I called the server over to rave about my meal while my friend explained how much  of a picky eater I am. I ordered the Jambalasi Shrimp w/ Chandon-Bennie Garlic Butter with a side of rice and peas and steamed cabbage. I don’t know what’s in that sauce but I’m going back and I’m taking my husband! He’s a huge Caribbean foodie and I need him to experience their food. Now I know there’s more offerings on the menu but when a restaurant has you at the first meal a lot needs to be said. The shrimp were tender and on the large side. That sauce was so good I had my friend taste some and she was equally impressed. My rice was perfect, as was my shredded steamed cabbage. My friends oxtails looked like they were made with love and please know I don’t give that compliment lightly. You know the chef(s) in that kitchen take a lot of pride and put much care into their food. It wasn’t salty at all, everything was flavorful and spoke to my soul. Can you hear my joy Google? Lol. The ONLY downside was when I went to pay they didn’t accept Discover and that was the only cc I had on me and it was NOT a pay week 😒 so a sister was running on fumes. Thankfully my friend was able to cover my meal for me.

I had walked past Sugarcane for about a full year before finally coming here to eat a couple of weeks ago. It's always packed and full of a lively crowd. I must say, my first time was pretty good!  HANDS DOWN, the food was onnnn pointtt. I ordered the Rasta Pasta with chicken, which was like $16, and let me tell y'all...I was pleasantly surprised to see how much food was brought out on that plate! I don't play, I like to eat, and I finished my whole plate, which astonished my friend. For $16, I got a LOT of food, and it was very delicious. I also got a Sorrel Sangria type drink, and it was tasty. It didn't taste like much at first, but the drink creeps up on you a bit!  On the wait time: this is the part that requires patience. As I said, everytime I walk past here, it is packed (which I now know is for good reason), but that waiting time is serious business. I got there with three small groups of folks ahead of me and waited an hour. My friend and I bided time in Bleachers next door and weren't starving, so there was no big fuss from us. But my understanding from one of the folks ahead of us is that even with a reservation, the waiting time is still extensive. We had the hostess call us when a table was ready, which is at least considerate of honoring our wanting to patron there, but my ultimate hope is that Sugarcane may opt for a bigger space in the future. They have good business, and it'd surely be better for its customers!
